  "title": "Kindergarten Care (KCare) Supervisor",
  "description": "<p>KCare Supervisory function:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Ensure the smooth running of the centre operations.</li>\n  <li>Plan and implement weekly schedules and programmes for the KCare children and ensure that programmes are delivered based on (MOE) Ministry of Education guidelines.</li>\n  <li>Plan and manage the staff scheduling, ensure staff (including programme staff and support staff) to children ratio is maintained at all times.</li>\n  <li>Inform and update MOE Kindergarten (MK) of all activities in a timely manner.</li>\n  <li>Be a mentor to staff as well as a team player.</li>\n  <li>Build strong partnerships and rapport with the following stakeholders, namely the children, parents, school personnel and the relevant authorities.</li>\n  <li>Plan outreach programmes and excursions for the children during the school holidays.</li>\n  <li>Conduct surveys with parents/ guardians to evaluate the services provided by the KCare Centre on a half-yearly basis.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Job Requirements of KCare Supervisor:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At the minimum, hold a Diploma in Early Childhood Care and Education – (DECCE-T) or an ECDA recognised equivalent obtained in the English medium.</li>\n  <li>Preferable to have leadership experience in a pre-school setting.</li>\n  <li>Experience in KCare or MOE Kindergarten advantageous.</li>\n  <li>Required language(s): English: Must excel in both written and verbal.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Office and Goggle Workspace</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Candidate should possess the following:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Active communication skills</li>\n  <li>Effective leadership and supervisory skills</li>\n  <li>Able to multi-task in a vibrant school environment</li>\n  <li>Able to manage centre's operations, budget, income and expenditure</li>\n  <li>Able to communicate effectively and manage your team of programme and support staff</li>\n  <li>Required Skill(s): leadership, manpower management, childcare, programme planning, lesson planning, coordination, programme execution, operation planning, strong communication skills</li>\n</ul>",
